{"word":"οἰνοχοέω","slug":"οἰνοχοέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰνοχοέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἰνοχόος'><el>οἰνοχόος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to pour out wine for drinking</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>νέκταρ ἐωινοχόει</el> <i>she was pouring out</i> nectar <i>for wine</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}